Rating: 1
I would make it again (and have) with the following changes: Saute shrimp when risotto is almost done. Add lemon juice and lemon zest to the risotto. Do not stir in the shrimp, but rather make a well in the dished up risotto and ladle in the scampi and the juiced then top it with some parm cheese and a little chopped ital. parsley. To mix it up, add in some asparagus as a side or in it. As is this is the most beige, uninviting, borezville meal. The shrimp get lost if you mix them in. The risotto needs some sprucing and lemon and cheese... how can you go wrong? You HAVE to cook the shrimp at the end. The shrimp will continue to cook in their sauce and then if you add them and cook for yet another 5 minutes those shrimp are effectively balls of rubberbands. Cooking at the last minute solves that. The creator of this recipe needs to find another job. As is, the recie is complete rubbish.

